.\" Guardian configuration man-page
.TH GUARDIAN 1 "April 2015" @PACKAGE_VERSION@ "Guardian Documentation"
.SH NAME
guardian \- Guardian Command-line utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
guardian
[
.IR options
]
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
The guardian command-line utility provides an interface to the guardiand
daemon process. It can be used to query, and configure the daemon.
.SH OPTIONS
.
The
.B guardian
command line utility understands the following command line options.
.TP 3
.B
-h  --help
Display command usage information
.TP 3
.B
-v  --verbose
Run in verbose mode
.TP 3
.B
-V  --version
Show version information
.TP 3
.B
-i  --interactive
Interactive Menu
.TP 3
.B
-s  --silent
Silent mode
.SH QUERY LANGUAGE
.TP 3
.B
connect user[:password][@host[:port]]
Connect to a server, if ommitted, host defaults to localhost,
port defaults to 1234.
.TP 3
.B
disconnect
Disconnect from a server
.TP 3
.B
exit
Close the shell.
